Parliament, Monday 15 July 2019 – The Speaker of the National Assembly, Ms Thandi Modise, and the Chairperson of the National Council of Provinces (NCOP), Mr Amos Masondo, will table Parliament’s Budget Vote in the National Assembly and NCOP respectively tomorrow afternoon.
	
	Debate on Vote 2: Parliament will be debated at 14.00 tomorrow in both the National Assembly Chamber and the National Council of Provinces Chamber.
	
	DETAILS OF BUDGET VOTE 2 ARE AS FOLLOWS:
	
	DATE: TUESDAY, 16 JUNE 2019
	TIME:14.00
	VENUES: NATIONAL ASSEMBLY AND NCOP CHAMBERS, PARLIAMENT
	
	Media who do not have parliamentary media access permits or photographers wishing to cover the Budget Vote in the National Assembly and NCOP Chambers should send their details to Mlindi Mpindi (mmpindi@parliament.gov.za, 081 716 7329) and copy mdlula@parliament.gov.za
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICAEnquiries: Moloto Mothapo – 082 370 6930 MPs have freedom of speech in Parliament, as long as they keep within the parliamentary rules. They cannot be prosecuted, arrested, imprisoned or be expected to pay damages for anything they say, produce or submit in Parliament or its committees.Read more